Class SearchProcess

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Related<CategorizedComponent>, Spatialized<DynamicSpace<SystemComponent>>, MultipleDataTrackerHolder<Metadata>, TwProcess, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sealable
    public class SearchProcess
extends AbstractRelationProcess
    Processes for searching the SystemComponent lists to establish relations between them. The difference with RelationProcess is that here we do not have relations yet, so we look for pairs of SystemComponents to establish a relation between them NB: this Process should not have datatrackers !
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 16 janv. 2020

      • setPermanentRelations

        public void setPermanentRelations​(java.util.Collection<SystemComponent> newComps,
                                  ComponentContainer comm,
                                  long time,
                                  long dtime)
        Establish permanent relations between SystemComponents at their creation time. Caution: the list of new SystemComponents passed as an argument may contain components of any category set, not necessarily compatible with this searchProcess (hence the late test for categories, ie at each SystemComponent level). The comm arguments contains all SystemComponents found in newComps.
        Parameters:
        newComps - a list of newly created components
        comm - the arena container, which contains all already present components
